 Minimum Job Requirements:
 Bachelor’s degree in a numerate discipline e.g. Data Science, Actuarial Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering, or Computer Science with a strong computer programming component;
 At least 8 of years working experience, with extensive hands-on experience in developing AI and Machine Learning solutions;
 Proven hands-on experience in the use of at least one advanced data analysis platform (e.g. Python, R, SAS);
 Exposure to all stages of data analytics project lifecycle (scope definition, data requirements, extraction, exploration, transformation, solution development, tracking);
 Demonstrable understanding of data quality risks and ability to carry out necessary exploratory data analysis and quality checks to validate results obtained;
 Knowledge of a variety of machine learning techniques (clustering, decision tree, random forest, artificial neural networks, etc.);
 Tenacious, with a desire to ‘get to the bottom’ of things with sound logical reasoning and deep analytical ability;
 Excellent relationship management, strong team building, and the ability to work across business units and functions to drive positive business outcomes;
 Sound knowledge of programming in SQL or other programming experience;
 Articulate, with excellent oral and written communication skills. Adaptable, able to interact and build strong relationships with people from a diverse range of backgrounds;
 Fast learner with a willing attitude. Intellectually rigorous, with strong analytical skills and a passion for data;
 Experience in big data environment and tools such as Hadoop, Hive, Datameer is desirable
